{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|1Ti|2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","chapter":2,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":1,"text":"First of all, then, I urge that petitions, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgivings be made for everyone,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":2,"text":"for kings and all those who are in authority, so that we may lead a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and dignity.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":3,"text":"This is good, and it pleases God our Savior,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":4,"text":"who wants everyone to be saved and to come to the knowledge of the truth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":5,"text":"For there is one God and one mediator between God and mankind, the man Christ Jesus,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":6,"text":"who gave himself as a ransom for all, a testimony at the proper time.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":7,"text":"For this I was appointed a herald, an apostle (I am telling the truth; I am not lying), and a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":8,"text":"Therefore, I want the men in every place to pray, lifting up holy hands without anger or argument.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":9,"text":"Also, the women are to dress themselves in modest clothing, with decency and good sense, not with elaborate hairstyles, gold, pearls, or expensive apparel,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":10,"text":"but with good works, as is proper for women who profess to worship God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":11,"text":"A woman is to learn quietly with full submission.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":12,"text":"I do not allow a woman to teach or to have authority over a man; instead, she is to remain quiet.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":13,"text":"For Adam was formed first, then Eve.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":14,"text":"And Adam was not deceived, but the woman was deceived and transgressed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","bookOrder":53,"chapter":2,"verse":15,"text":"But she will be saved through childbearing, if they continue in faith, love, and holiness, with good sense.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ti","chapter":2,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,7,8],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Instructions on Prayer"},{"beforeVerse":8,"text":"Instructions to Men and Women"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"First of all, then, I urge that petitions, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgivings be made for everyone, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"for kings and all those who are in authority, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 6:10","book":"Ezr","chapter":6,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 13:1","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 2:1","book":"1Co","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that we may lead a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 1:3","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":3,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" and dignity. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 3:4","book":"1Ti","chapter":3,"verse":4,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 2:7","book":"Tit","chapter":2,"verse":7,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezr 6:10","book":"Ezr","chapter":6,"verse":10},{"label":"Rm 13:1","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":1},{"label":"1Co 2:1","book":"1Co","chapter":2,"verse":1},{"label":"2Pt 1:3","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":3},{"label":"1Tm 3:4","book":"1Ti","chapter":3,"verse":4},{"label":"Ti 2:7","book":"Tit","chapter":2,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ti:2:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"This is good, and it pleases God our Savior, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 1:1","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Tm 1:1"